DHCP Poisoning with Responder

- Spoofing DHCP responses can permanently poison a victim’s routing information, 
  offering a stealthier alternative to ARP poisoning.

- It requires precise knowledge of the target network’s configuration.

- Running the attack: 
  ./Responder.py -I eth0 -Pdv

- This method can effectively capture NTLMv1/2 hashes, but it requires careful handling
   to avoid network disruption.

